<TITLE> BCB coach Dipu Roy, wife arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 8 (bdnews24.com)  RAB Wednesday arrested Dipu Roy Chowdhury, a coach for Bangladesh Cricket Board, and his wife for their alleged roles in illegal migration of workers into foreign countries, police said. Gulshan police sub-inspector Zia Latiful Islam told bdnews24.com that the couple had been arrested in an evening raid on a house in Banani. The officers of RAB-1 took the former national cricketer and wife Arifa Roy Chowdhury, nicknamed Putul, to Gulshan Police Station. RAB officers seized four passports and a can of beer from them, Islam said. A case was underway to file against the two under the Passport Act, he said. BCB spokesman Ahmed Sajjadul Alam Boby told bdnews24.com: "I heard he was arrested. I think the BCB will do something about it. We have to wait until morning (Thursday)." bdnews24.
